===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# The territory between [[Central Europe|Central]] and [[Eastern Europe]] inhabited by [[Rusyn]]s, on the slopes of the Carpathian Mountains in parts of Ukraine, Poland and Slovakia.
#: {{syn|en|Carpathian Ruthenia|Zakarpattia|Subcarpathian Rus|Carpatho-Ukraine}}
# {{lb|en|historical}} Lands inhabited by Ukrainians ([[Ruthenian]]s) of the former Austrian Empire kingdom of [[Galicia]] (1772–1918), corresponding to parts of Western Ukraine.
# {{lb|en|historical}} Western portions of East Slavic lands, including the principalities of Galicia-Volhynia and Kyiv, which united with Lithuania and Poland (14th c–1772), corresponding to what is now Ukraine and Belarus.
#: {{syn|en|Red Ruthenia|Galicia-Volhynia}}
# {{lb|en|historical}} [[Rus]], an East Slavic medieval state (880–12th c), corresponding to what is now Ukraine and Belarus, as well as western Russia.
#: {{syn|en|Kievan Rus|Kievan Russia}}

